        "title": "New Course - OpenShift on OpenStack",
        "excerpt":"For those who caught the OpenShift on OpenStack bug at OpenStack Summit Berlin &amp; want to know more, check out my latest Linux Academy course - aptly named OpenShift on OpenStack!  You’ll get a full walkthrough on how to quickly deploy your own OpenStack Queens cloud using OpenStack PackStack, then launch an OpenShift cluster with Keystone, Cinder, &amp; Neutron integrations using Keith Tenzer’s OpenShift-on-OpenStack123 playbooks. Once your OoO123 cluster is running, we’ll practice OpenShift migrations, disaster recovery, &amp; more. If you don’t have a Linux Academy subscription yet, now is a GREAT time to sign up to take advantage of 33% off #CyberMonday deals, so what are you waiting for?? ","categories": ["linuxacademy"],
